# BUG-447-CASCADE-1 — files exempt from the
# `signacare-rules/no-onclick-on-mui-container` rule during the BUG-447
# campaign. Each child commit (BUG-447-medications through BUG-447-misc-
# residual; run order 1..15) removes its file(s) as the violations are
# fixed.
#
# *** CAMPAIGN CLOSED 2026-04-29 *** — child 15/15 (BUG-447-misc-
# residual) was the final cycle. All 15 children + 7 cascade follow-ups
# closed. The cascade-1 ESLint rule now fires across the entire
# `apps/web/src/**` tree without exemption. This file is preserved as
# the historical record of the campaign sequence; any new path entry
# triggers `R-FIX-BUG-447-PARENT-CLOSE-ALLOWLIST-EMPTY` to fail CI.
#
# When this file is empty (apart from comments), BUG-447 is structurally
# complete: the rule fires across the entire `apps/web/src/**` tree
# without exemption.
#
# Format: one path per line (relative to repo root). Paths ending with
# `/` are directory prefixes (any descendant matches). Other paths are
# exact matches. `#` lines and blank lines are ignored.
#
# Initial population: enumerated by AST scan on 2026-04-27 — the exact
# 40 files (71 violations) that contain `<Box|Paper|Card|Typography
# onClick>` violations as detected by the rule itself running against
# the live tree. The AST-accurate count supersedes the original
# catalogue claim of 36/67.
#
# Per-child mapping (which child removes which file):

# BUG-447-medications (run 1) — closed; allowlist entry removed.

# BUG-447-patient-detail-shell (run 2)

